result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin T. Tomlinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ma/mk] Case called at 8:19 AM 
Defendant Austin T. Tomlinson appeared by video from the Rock County Jail, in custody.  Attorney Sylvie Dahnert in court for Austin T. Tomlinson.  Attorney Krysta Parson in court for State of Wisconsin. 
The Court verifies with Mr. Tomlinson that he understands he has the right to be present in the courtroom for sentencing, and he is waiving this right. 

Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; plea of " GUILTY " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2.
Sentencing recommendations/ arguments given by Counsel 

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Tomlinson to 30 days in the Jefferson County Jail with Huber privileges consecutive. 
Days credit for time already served:  2 days. 

The Court STAYS this sentence and places Mr. Tomlinson on Probation for one year with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment 
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--to pay costs and DNA surcharge
